description: This comic is mainly a program and not much else.  The front and back covers are amazing examples of art and there is an advance preview on the inside of the book for a comic known as Mindfield.  It is only four pages and not much in depth but it is about a CIA created team of telepathic agents used to fight the war on terrorism.  The heroes are able to see in the minds of their targets and see through their eyes.

description: Sins of Youth part 10 of 12. Having traded names and updated their looks to fit their new ages, Wonder Woman and Wonder Girl go to the gods for help. Unfortunately, they wind up getting into even more trouble when Apollo sends them to face a Cyclops with the powers of Medusa! One look at this creature, and their age troubles will become permanent, because the Amazon pair will turn to stone! Meanwhile, Klarion visits Wonder Woman's WonderDome and takes the Sphinx!
name: Coming of Age

description:
The Wolverine Files presents the complete story of the most reluctant of the X-Men. Assembled by the intelligence operatives at S.H.I.E.L.D. (Supreme Headquarters International Espionage Law Enforcement Division) this wide ranging dossier on this most powerful mutant delves into every aspect of his life - from his creation by the Weapon X project to his interaction with the other members of the X-Men - no part of his life has been left uninspected.

Back Blurb

The enclosed is a top secret compilation of all known facts about the mutant called Wolverine (a/k/a Logan, Weapon X, Patch, the Runt). This report, generated by the concerted effort of SHIELD agents, i intended for the eyes of SHIELD personnel only, and is not to be copies, distributed, disseminated, or in any other way leaked to te general public due to the delicate nature of the information herein. It details Wolverine's origins, career, friends, allies, in all manner of specifics.

Be aware that representatives from Simon & Schuster publishing have been sniffing around, endeavoring to obtain this information through the Freedom of Information Act. We cannot begin to imagine the tremendous, even incalculable, damage that would be sustained by both Wolverine and by our information-gathering forces should this report wind up for purchase in local bookstores. Let us hope such an event never comes to pass.

Table of Contents

  • Origins
  • History
  • Territories
  • His Allies
  • The Women In His Life
  • Enemies
  • Travels In Time And Space
  • Alternate Realities
  • Supporting Data

description: This book, "written" by Iris Allen, reporter and wife of the Silver Age Flash, chronicles the life and times of Barry Allen, who died saving the world during Crisis on Infinite Earths. The volume retells in comic book form and in text/picture book form many of Flash's past adventures, including his battles with Reverse Flash, who attempted to kill Iris.
name: The Life Story of The Flash

description: Sins of Youth part 7 of 12. Is the world ready for (gasp!) a mature, thoughtful Impulse? The Flashes have been assigned to spin-doctor Young Justice's bad press by conducting the fastest media junket ever, but when crisis after crisis keeps them from clearing their names, it only makes matters worse. Meanwhile, Linda Park and Wally West's honeymoon goes south when Linda discovers she's now married to Kid Flash, and Captain Cold gets a chilly reception from Klarion!
